Architecture plan for the 22-issue implementation sequence

Project shape
- Vite + React + TypeScript single-page app with Tailwind CSS.
- Pure TypeScript autograd/training core under src/lib so it can be unit-tested without React.
- React components under src/components, grouped by layout, math, network visualization, controls, and panels.
- Vitest for unit and component-level tests; Playwright for the final walkthrough.

Proposed file organization
- src/main.tsx: React entrypoint.
- src/App.tsx: top-level app composition and shell wiring.
- src/styles/index.css: Tailwind imports and base theme tokens.
- src/lib/autograd/value.ts: scalar Value node, graph links, forward ops, gradient fields, labels, metadata.
- src/lib/autograd/ops.ts: arithmetic, activation, and loss helpers with local backward closures.
- src/lib/autograd/backprop.ts: topological traversal and reverse-mode gradient propagation.
- src/lib/network/preset.ts: fixed network topology, preset weights, sample input, target, and labels.
- src/lib/network/stepController.ts: deterministic forward -> loss -> backward -> update state machine.
- src/lib/network/types.ts: shared node, edge, phase, and step types used by core and UI.
- src/components/math/MathRender.tsx: KaTeX wrapper.
- src/components/network/NetworkDiagram.tsx: static SVG graph, active node/edge highlighting, animation hooks.
- src/components/panels/MathPanel.tsx: live chain-rule display for current step.
- src/components/panels/ExplanationPanel.tsx: concise explanation for the current step.
- src/components/controls/StepControls.tsx: next, previous, reset controls.
- src/components/layout/AppShell.tsx: responsive final layout binding diagram and panels.
- tests/unit: autograd, network, controller, and update tests.
- tests/e2e: end-to-end walkthrough test.

Shared types
- Value: scalar data, grad, parents, op name, backward callback, stable id, optional label.
- GraphNode and GraphEdge: UI-safe view model derived from Value/network state.
- NetworkState: weights, activations, loss, gradients, current step index, history snapshots.
- Step: phase, active nodes, active edges, explanation key, math expression data, action payload.

Issue dependency map
- #1 is the project foundation.
- #2 depends on #1 and establishes the visual shell used by later UI issues.
- #3 depends on #1/#2 and enables #16.
- #4 depends on #1 and should happen before broad implementation to stabilize tooling.
- #5, #6, #7 build the autograd core in order.
- #8 depends on #5-#7.
- #9 depends on the core shape from #5-#7.
- #10 depends on #5 and #7, and feeds #11.
- #11 depends on #9 and #10.
- #12 depends on #11.
- #13 depends on #9 for the fixed topology.
- #14 depends on #11 and #13.
- #15 depends on #14.
- #16 depends on #3 and #11.
- #17 depends on #11.
- #18 depends on #11 and feeds final composition.
- #19 depends on #13-#18.
- #20 depends on #19.
- #21 depends on #19 and should run after the full UI exists.
- #22 depends on #20/#21 and finalizes production build/deploy readiness.

Key design decisions
- Keep the autograd core framework-agnostic and deterministic; React should render snapshots rather than mutate graph objects directly.
- Store step history as serializable snapshots so previous/reset controls are simple and testable.
- Use stable ids for nodes and edges from the fixed network definition; UI highlighting and tests should not depend on array order.
- Let Value backward closures implement only local derivatives, while backprop owns graph traversal and gradient accumulation.
- Prefer SVG for the fixed network diagram because it provides precise layout, accessible labels, and straightforward animation targets.
- Keep KaTeX rendering behind one reusable component so math sanitization, error handling, and display mode stay consistent.
- Keep explanations data-driven from step metadata where practical, avoiding hard-coded logic scattered across panels.
